race.comment: DANCING JUICE (9) was racing well at the provincials and was well supported before the nose defeat at Tatura. Has weight relief this time around and if he can run up to his recent figures, he'll be hard to hold out. CALYPSO KING (4) is also racing well enough to feature. Steps out to this distance for the first time and is sure to be strong to the line. PARVATI PARTY (7) is up to this at best and has won a jumpout since the plain effort here first-up. Has some key gear tweaks and quick improvement is likely. TACTFULL (10) spiked his figures beaten 1L in stronger at Traralgon. The wet track suited, but he will be around the mark on that effort.
